### Paddokk API Test Requests - Better-Auth EdDSA Integration

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5037
# Get your token from:
# 1. Login to your app at http://localhost:3000
# 2. Open Browser DevTools > Application/Storage
# 3. Find JWT token in localStorage or cookies
# 4. Paste it below:
@token = PASTE_YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Health Check (no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/ping

###

### 2. Check JWKS (verify better-auth keys)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/jwks

###

### 3. Debug Token (decode without validation)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/debug-token
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 4. Test Authentication (validates EdDSA token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/test-auth
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 5. Get Current User
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 6. Get User by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 7. Update Current User
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "displayName": "Updated Name",
  "bio": "Updated bio via API"
}
